@<html>
<title>
Surfing the Web by Voice
</title>
<body>
<a href=index.html><i>Back to index</i></a>
<h1>
Surfing the Web by Voice
</h1>
<strong>
Charles Hemphill and Philip Thrift
</strong>

<p><b>One-line summary: Speaker-independent, continuous, real-time,
dynamic grammar WWW browser.</b>

</p>

<h2>Overview/Main Points</h2>
<ul>
  <li> Dynamic grammar - generates grammar on the fly for web pages
  <li> Allows pages to be customized for speech
  <li> Always-available speakable hotlist
  <li> Easy-to-understand grammars
  <li> Speaker-indep., continuous, real-time
</ul>

<h2>Relevance</h2>

WWW browsing is one of the killer apps for the Pad.  We'd like our WWW
browser to have all the features this system has.

<h2>Flaws</h2>
<ul>
  <li> Integrated as part of a browser (NCSA Mosaic), so not portable
  <li> Uses large dictionary (250,000 words)
  <li> Has problems with numbers, non-standard acronyms, invented
       words, and novel use of punctuation, abbreviations, etc.
</ul>

<hr>
<a href=index.html><i>Back to index</i></a>

</body></html>
